---
description: Project scope, ignore paths, and coding guidance for PHP/Laravel HRIS
alwaysApply: true
---

# Project Scope

Focus only on:

- app/
- routes/
- config/
- resources/
- database/
- modules/
- public/index.php

# Ignore Dependencies

Never scan:

- vendor/
- node_modules/
- bower_components/

# Ignore Generated Files

Never read generated or compiled files:

- public/build/
- dist/
- build/
- target/
- bootstrap/cache/
- storage/framework/
- storage/cache/

# Ignore Logs

Never scan:

- storage/logs/
- logs/
- *.log

# Ignore Environment Files

Never read:

- .env
- .env.*
- *.key

# Ignore Version Control

Never scan:

- .git/

# Ignore Media Files

Never scan media or binary files:

- *.png
- *.jpg
- *.jpeg
- *.webp
- *.mp4
- *.mov
- *.zip
- *.tar
- *.gz

# Coding Guidance

Prefer:

- existing project patterns
- service classes
- repository pattern if available
- Laravel conventions
- reusable functions
- minimal file changes

Avoid:

- unnecessary refactors
- changing unrelated files
- scanning the whole repository
